<b>The Skinny on Haste Stacking - </b>9/26/02 12:58:03 PM<br>~ <b>Devamaru</b><blockquote>Here's the basic rule on haste stacking:<br><br>Any given character can only have two haste effects on them at once: Item haste, and Spell Haste. Bardsongs count as spells. If you have multiple hastes of the same type on, then whichever is greater will take effect. So, if you have Quickness (30% haste) and Anthem de Arms (10%) in effect, then your haste will be 30%.<br><br>But Deva, I hear you say, it DOES stack! I see both icons! Yes, you do, and the spell and song will not overwrite each other. That is because the other componant of Anthem (the Strength bonus) WILL be in effect. However, the haste component will not. You're not swinging any faster with Quickness and Anthem than you are with just Quickness. Anthem becomes, in that case, a STR boost song.<br><br>There are four song exceptions to this situation, and all of them are level 50+. There are two &quot;Ervaj&quot; songs which were released with Velious, Melody of Ervaj (Level 50) and Composition of Ervaj (Level 60). Both of these songs require that the bard have a brass instrument equipped to play them. They give a small haste bonus (5% and 10% each) which will stack with other spell hastes. However, considering how small the bonus is and that you have to have a horn equipped to sing them, these songs are not very useful in most circumstances.<br><br>Two songs were released with Luclin which are substantially better. They are the &quot;Vah Shir&quot; songs, Battlecry of the Vah Shir (Level 52) and Warsong of the Vah Shir (Level 60). Both of these songs will give decent haste bonuses (15% and 25% respectively), are Singing based so you don't have to have an instrument equipped to sing them, and also are the only songs currently in the game which will allow your group members to exceed the haste cap.<br><br>Chances are that when you are grouped with an Enchanter or Shaman, their haste is going to be better than yours. However, that doesn't automatically mean you shouldn't offer to sing haste. Yours is mana free, after all, and yours has other effects which can be useful. The idea is to coordinate with your other group members to see what is the most efficient way to do things. Just understand that before level 50, the haste in your songs won't stack with other spell forms of haste.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
